# The memQL SDK packages are published to GitHub Packages, not the public npm
# registry. Point both scopes at npm.pkg.github.com; every other dependency
# (react, vite, ...) still resolves from the default registry.
#
#   @__PRODUCT_ORG__/__PRODUCT__-sdk   -- this product's generated SDK (the
#                                         engine's sdk-gen produces it from
#                                         core DSL + this repo's dsl/__PRODUCT__/)
#   @znasllc-io/memql-sdk-core         -- the shared memQL runtime it extends
#
# The starter shell does NOT yet import either package (it ships a thin local
# client + a local generated concepts module so it builds standalone), so no
# token is needed to `npm ci` the scaffold. Once you wire the published SDK
# (README 'SDK resolution'), export NODE_AUTH_TOKEN to a GitHub token with
# read:packages for both scopes.
@__PRODUCT_ORG__:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
@znasllc-io:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}
